    <note>Zeng(1) Shaoxian [12709] Fujian TZ, 149.49a has him as grandson (sun) of Kang [1705], which is probably an error for yuansun, which would make him a fourth generation descendant by TZ conventions and a fifth generation descendants by other conventions including RMH. This comes out pretty good at 30 years a generation. Other citations (q.v.) for this lineage confirm that Shaoxian was a brother of Yingfu [12770], Mengfu [12771], Bingsun [12809] and Zihao [19703]. Sanshan zhi, 31.3b.</note>
